(2) Very extensive use of verbal nouns and adjectives—

(i) verbals in -io, These are exceedingly common in Livy, being-not only used (a) to express the means or manner of an action (as in 5. 17. 1, 3. expiatio . . . procuratio). But (b) to express a simple act or its result. This is especially the case in descriptive passages, e. g.—

7. 10. 8. non cantus, non exsultatio, armorumque agitatio vana.
